\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. B. divionensis} Jordan,{\i  Diagn. }{\b 1}: 305 (1864). Rhizome long, woody, terminating in a rosette or divided and producing rosette-bearing branches; stems up to 25 cm. Basal leaves 5-7 × 1-1·5 cm, densely puberulent or canescent, densely rosulate, cuneate or spathulate, with 1-3 large, opposite, acute teeth on each side; apex subacute; cauline leaves few. Inflorescence branched, somewhat dense. Petals 6 mm. Silicula 6-7 × 9-11 mm. 2n = 18.{\i  Limestone rocks. • E.C. France }({\i near Dijon}). Ga.
\par

