\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. B. coronopifolia} L.,{\i  Mantissa Alt.} 255 (1771) ({\i B. lima }Reichenb., {\i B. tarraconensis} Sennen). Stems up to 30 cm, hispid to hirsute. Basal leaves 3-4 × 1·5 cm, hispid or hirsute, laxly rosulate, pinnatifid, with 2-4 long, remote, somewhat acute lobes on each side; lower cauline leaves about as large as the basal, with large teeth, the upper linear-setaceous. Inflorescence several times branched. Sepals 2·5 mm; petals 5 mm. Silicula 5-7 × 9-13 mm. 2n = 18. •{\i  S. & S.C. France and E. Spain; N. Italy.} Ga Hs It.
\par

