\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. B. intricata} Jordan, {\i Diagn. }{\b 1}: 308 (1864). Stems up to 50 cm, intricately branched from the base, the branches open and patent in a corymbose manner, hirsute below. Basal leaves 6-8 × 1·5-2 cm, pubescent, oblong, pinnatilobed, with 3-5 ovate, slightly acute lobes on each side; cauline leaves lobed or dentate. Raceme quite dense, elongating during anthesis. Petals 4·5 mm. Silicula 5 × 9 mm. •{\i  S.E. France} ({\i S. & W. of Lyon}). Ga.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. B. apricorum} Jordan, {\i op. cit.} 307 (1864). Stems 35-40 cm, sparsely hispid or hirsute. Basal leaves 4-6 × 1-1·5 cm, hispid-setose, oblong-spathulate, with 3 or 4 large, obtuse teeth on each margin; cauline leaves semi-amplexicaul, with large teeth. Sepals 2-3 mm; petals 5-6 mm. Silicula 7 × 10-11 mm.{\i  Dry places. • S.E. France.} Ga.
\par

